analysis: The documents all pertain to the modification or revocation of previous land orders, withdrawals, and reservations. They describe specific land tracts, often identified by meridian, township, range, and section, and specify the purpose of the original order (e.g., power sites, reservoir sites, soil conservation, magnesium production, water reserves, target range, airport). The documents involve actions such as revoking previous orders, modifying existing orders, withdrawing land from public use, and reserving land for specific purposes. The sentiment is neutral, as they are legal and administrative actions.
title: Land Order Modifications and Revocations
